# Versal AI Edge VD100 — Linux Platform

Custom Yocto Linux on the Alinx VD100 (XCVE2302-SFVA784-1LP-E-S) — from Vivado project to a fully booting, production-grade embedded Linux platform with peripheral support.

> No VCK190. No MATLAB. No Simulink. Bare-metal VHDL, a UART, and a debugger's mindset.

---

## The Platform

```
Vivado 2025.2
    └─ CIPS configuration + PL design → XSA export
        └─ lopper / sdtgen → System Device Tree (vd100_sdt)
            └─ Yocto Scarthgap + meta-vd100
                └─ VD100 Linux 1.0
                    ├─ PLM → U-Boot → systemd-boot → Linux
                    ├─ Ethernet, USB, I2C, GPIO, Sysmon
                    └─ C++ application deployment via RPM
```

---

## Repository Structure

| Path | Contents |
|---|---|
| `psHelloWorld/hardware/` | Vivado 2025.2 project — CIPS configuration, PL hello world design, XSA export |
| `psHelloWorld/software/vd100_sdt/` | System Device Tree generated from XSA via lopper/sdtgen |
| `psHelloWorld/software/hello_world/` | Vitis bare-metal application |
| `psHelloWorld/software/myhelloworld/` | Custom bare-metal application |
| `yocto/meta-vd100/` | Custom Yocto layer — distro config, BSP, machine config, DTS patches, recipes |
| `yocto/build/` | Build environment — `local.conf`, `bblayers.conf` |
| `images/` | Terminal screenshots and boot photos |

---

## Board

| Item | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Device** | XCVE2302-SFVA784-1LP-E-S |
| **Family** | Versal AI Edge Series |
| **PS** | Dual-core Cortex-A72 @ 959 MHz |
| **DDR** | 2 GiB |
| **eMMC** | 29.6 GiB |
| **Cost** | ~AU$1,285 — accessible alternative to the AU$15,000+ VCK190 |

---

## Confirmed Working Peripherals

| Peripheral | Status |
|---|---|
| SD card (via TXS02612 level shifter) | ✅ |
| Ethernet GEM | ✅ |
| USB XHCI (host mode) | ✅ |
| I2C0 / I2C1 / I2C2 | ✅ |
| LM75 board temperature sensor | ✅ |
| EEPROM Atmel 24C04 | ✅ |
| Versal sysmon (die temperature + voltages) | ✅ |
| GPIO — PS_LED1 (LPD_MIO25) | ✅ |
| PMC GPIO | ✅ |
| RTC | ✅ |

